properties.description:
# Access Camping (for campers who want to come and go)

* Access 9 - 5, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday, Monday, Tuesday
* Pink permit required - This is the come-and-go camping areas.
* At 5pm each festival night, the welcome gate will be locked and chain barrier at Tony’s Tip gate will be erected, to be reopened at 9am the following morning.

https://www.confest.org.au/prepare/vehicle-parking

properties.name: Camping Car-Free
properties.label: Car-free
properties.description:
# Car Free camping (forested areas) 

* No Vehicles Allowed - Park your Car in Yellow Car parking and be bussed to Blue Car Free Camping
* **Car free camping exists for many reasons including:**
    * Caring for our Land – driving on the lower flood plain compacts the soil, restricts natural regrowth, creates ruts and reduces tree root vitality.
    * Safety – Areas which are free of cars are safer for everyone especially children. It also ensures the narrower tracks on the flood plain remain free from vehicles in the event that a fire truck or ambulance requires access. 
    * Atmosphere – Not everyone has a car and not everyone wants to be surrounded by the modern world when camping at ConFest. Providing areas for car free camping is attractive for many people and spaces including Tranquillity, Family and Arts.
    * Dust – It can get hot and dusty at ConFest. No cars means less dust.

https://www.confest.org.au/prepare/vehicle-parking

(Note: As discussed with Emma by mattcen in Facebook chat)

properties.name: Stay Put
properties.label: Stay Put
properties.description:
# Stay Put camping (for Recreational Vehicles only)

* Must be in by 5pm Thursday 18 April 2019
* Cannot leave till after midday Monday 22 April 2019
* Green permit required - For recreational vehicles, often abbreviated as RV, is a motor vehicle or trailer which includes living quarters designed for accommodation. 
* Types of RVs include motorhomes, campervans, caravans (also known as travel trailers and camper trailers), fifth-wheel trailers, popup campers and truck and van campers.
* People with vehicle permits for Stay-Put who arrive after this time can camp in the Access camping area.

https://www.confest.org.au/prepare/vehicle-parking
